article.headline: Lehigh 72, Albany 61
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Jose Olivero scored 17 points to lead four Mountain Hawks in double figures as Lehigh used clutch foul shooting to hold off Albany 72-61 on Tuesday night. The Mountain Hawks shot 9-for-10 from the foul line in the last two minutes of the game to hold off Albany, which used an 8-2 run in the middle of the second half capped by a jumper by Jamar Wilson to pull to 63-60. But Albany could muster only one point the rest of the way. Joe Knight scored 13 points while Nick Monserez added 12 and Kyle Neptune scored 11 for Lehigh (3-2). Lucious Jordan scored a game-high 19 points and Wilson added 15 for Albany (2-2). The Mountain Hawks shot 12-for-21 (57 percent) from the floor in the first half and 10-for-12 from the line on their way to a 36-24 halftime lead. The win gave Lehigh 16 consecutive wins at home.
